      "text": "Animation is widely understood as an aid to comprehension — but the evidence is more ambiguous than practitioners tend to acknowledge. This paper maps the conditions under which motion reduces cognitive load against those in which it introduces unwanted extraneous processing, with practical implications for transition design, progress indicators, and data visualisation.",
